PAUL ORUDE BAUCHI Results of the supplementary election carried out in 15 local government areas of Bauchi State indicate that the main opposition party, the People’s Democratic Party (PDP) is having an upper hand. As the news of the impending victory of PDP filters in with the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC) trailing in most polling units, hundreds of supporters of the PDP have converged on the entrance of the INEC office chanting victory songs. Singing in Hausa, they chanted saying Bauchi people don’t want you MA, pack and go, we want Laura, our son. As results from the local government come in, long convoys of vehicles with heavily-armed security personnel, the PDP supporters are breaking into frenzied jubilation The results announced in some polling units in the affected local governments are as follow: Kagadama ward PDP 358 APC 184 Ajili Gugulin Ward PDP 312 APC 111 Ajili Samadawa ward PDP 142 APC 61 Malar APU PDP 478 APC 101 Malar B PDP 224 APC 57 PU 009 Madara/Dunare/Kofar Jauro PDP 82 APC 112 Chara-chara Primary sch Azare PDP 121 APC 149 Gabarun ward PDP 155 APC 85 Unguwar Jaki PU PDP 240 APC 178 Zazika PDP 100 APC 75 Kwangi PDP 135 APC 232 Harodo PDP 124 APC 64 Baure PDP 194 APC 209 Kofar Fada ward PDP 261 APC 127 Rumfar Magama 003 PU PDP 212 APC 203 Jankude  PU PDP 46 APC 91 Memihefta Hannafari ward PDP 58 APC 74 Batak ward PDP 202 APC 87 Jamda ward PDP 244 APC 170 Wuro Gumbai PU 006 PDP 113 APC 87 Bara ward PDP 361 APC 119 11.Kirfi LGA K/Sarkin Yakin Bara, Bara PU 006 APC = 119 PDP = 360 Kofar Sarkin Gabarin PU (karamin akwati) APC = 119 PDP = 125 Kofar Sarkin Gabarin PU (       ) Salarma pri. Sch. Ribina PDP 247 APC 304 Zul Polling Unit PDP-428 APC-69 Gurungu Kofar Sarki PDP153 APC 164 Zirami PU PDP 114 APC 195 Gadaule PU PDP 132 APC 179 Gulbun ward PDP 197 APC 130 Faguji Ward PDP 96 APC 127 Hakatari Kariwa ward PDP 159 APC 137 Languram ward PDP 86 APC 152 PDP 312 APC 203 Total Votes Casts PDP 6,289 APC 4986 Difference 1,303 Verdict: PDP Wins Thre